From: gahingwoo <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 28/28] accel/rocket: rk3576 consolidate dispatch to the vendor-grammar single-kick (Phase A/B settled state)

Phase A/B and the BARE task_number=N experiments (FINDINGS.md, WHOLEGRAPH-
GRAMMAR.md, all 2026-07-05) settled the RK3576 dispatch question: a single
PC submit with TASK_CON.task_number = job->task_count (the vendor
rknpu_job_subcore_commit_pc grammar), one PC_OP_EN pulse, and mesa's
task regcmds packed contiguously at a fixed 64-byte-aligned stride
(PC_DATA_AMOUNT computed as (regcfg_amount+4+scale-1)/scale-1 so the PC's own
fetch advances into the next task) makes the PC genuinely walk the whole
chain -- TASK_STATUS advances (confirmed to 6), all four units engage
(exec_ever=0xf), DMA is clean, PC_DONE fires clean. Native BARE task_number=N
iteration (zero driver intervention during the run) reproduces the identical
result byte-for-byte. A live wtrace capture of the vendor's own multi-task
submit additionally confirmed PC_DMA_BASE_ADDR/TASK_DMA_BASE_ADDR = 0 in every
capture (task_number=2 and 8 alike) -- the vendor does NOT use a descriptor-
array/DMA-fetch mechanism; TASK_DMA_BASE_ADDR stays 0 here too, matching it.

None of this fixes the wall: every task after the first in a power session
computes empty (zero-point) regardless of dispatch mechanism -- chained,
natively-iterated, or (per the separate SPREAD-CONFIRM board result)
completely independent single-task submits. The remaining wall is the
CBUF->CSC->CMAC "consume-arm", a per-power-session resource that only a full
NPU power-cycle re-arms, not a dispatch/register/regcmd-grammar bug.

This patch removes the now-dead experimental module_param forks that
enumerated the alternatives (chain_task_number, wg_continuous flag,
bare_tasknum, wg_warm_chain, bisect, rekick_reset, audit_all, pw_weight_sram,
geom_all, conv0_twice, open_high, pp_alt, trailer_check, zero_out_bos,
spread_confirm, read_margin sweep, cbuf_reset variants, and related dump
helpers) now that each is independently concluded, and makes the settled
single-kick TASK_CON=job->task_count dispatch the unconditional default --
consolidation only, no behavioral change to the settled dispatch path itself.
Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
---
